   {:e #blake3 "54f11f1020a080a6d54e224e1c619d2aace0d1f261dd67c437cdbfc882c3e0ee" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: The definitive test suite proving C9 achieves 10/10. Must verify: proactive path (seed convergent findings), reactive path (steering-optimized observe subcommands), invariant formalization (INV-REFLEXIVE-006/007), concept naming quality, and the fixed-point property. FOUR TEST LAYERS: LAYER 1 — UNIT TESTS (24 tests): all_observations: (1) empty store, (2) 5 obs sorted by timestamp desc, (3) fields correct, (4) concept_name populated, (5) link_count correct. observe subcommands: (6) list groups by concept, (7) search ranks by composite score, (8) search empty returns empty, (9) show includes links, (10) recent respects limit, (11) creation backward compat. agent identity: (12) PID-based default, (13) BRAID_AGENT override, (14) explicit --agent override. concept naming: (15) distinguishing keywords differ from global keywords, (16) deterministic, (17) fallback to existing name on failure. scoring: (18) proptest: high-link high-confidence obs ranks above low-link low-confidence, (19) proptest: empty corroboration map produces identical score to original formula. LAYER 2 — INVARIANT VERIFICATION (5 tests): INV-REFLEXIVE-006: (20) 10 obs from 2 agents, braid observe search returns top 3 convergent. (21) braid observe list on 50 obs shows grouped themes with member counts. (22) braid observe show on obs with 3 links shows all targets. INV-REFLEXIVE-007 fixed-point: (23) find_agreement_clusters on observations ABOUT agreement clusters returns valid (possibly empty) result, no panic, no special case. (24) No C9 function has conditional branch on observation content type (grep verify: no 'meta' or 'domain' enum variant in C9 types). LAYER 3 — INTEGRATION TEST (tests/c9_second_order.rs, 3 scenarios): SCENARIO A (proactive): 3 AgentIds, same finding, seed orientation has Convergent findings with 3/3. SCENARIO B (reactive): 10 obs, 3 concepts, varying confidence/links, observe list groups correctly, search ranks by composite, show has graph context. SCENARIO C (fixed-point): Create observations about observations (meta-level). Run C9 functions on them. Verify same output format, no errors, no special cases. LAYER 4 — E2E SCRIPT (scripts/e2e_c9_complete.sh, 15 checks): (1) braid init. (2-4) 3 observations from 3 BRAID_AGENT values about same topic. (5) 1 unrelated observation. (6) braid observe list — ASSERT grouped, dominant cluster has 3+ members. (7) braid observe search 'stagnant' — ASSERT 2+ results ranked. (8) braid observe search 'unrelated' — ASSERT 1 result. (9) braid observe recent 2 — ASSERT 2 with concept tags. (10) braid observe show <entity> — ASSERT body + links + agent. (11) braid seed --task synthesize — ASSERT Convergent findings. (12) Verify concept display names are meaningful (not hash artifacts). (13) Create observation about observation-1 ('this corroborates the stagnation finding'). (14) braid observe show on meta-observation — ASSERT works identically to domain observation (fixed-point). (15) All exit codes 0. LOGGING: structured [C9-TEST] prefix, command/output/assertion/elapsed per step. On failure: dump store datom count, observation count by agent, concept inventory with names, agreement clusters, full seed output. DEPENDS-ON: C9-P4 (t-266f06d5), C9-P5 (t-0217080c), C9-P6 (t-4807b60b), C9-SPEC (t-1e1710d3). FILES: crates/braid-kernel/tests/c9_second_order.rs, scripts/e2e_c9_complete.sh, inline tests. EFFORT: 6h." :op :assert}
